rComments: Ashton is by far the most incredible professor I've ever had.  Had him by fluke in my first year and actively sought out his classes ever since.  He is a phenomenal man and a great educator; very approachable, extraordinarily intelligent and down to earth in his teachings.  If you have the opportunity to have him, you're a very luck student. :)

What a breath of fresh air in the U of O's otherwise stuffy English department! Down to earth, bold and inspirational, he wants his students to do well. Values creativity and new ideas. Not in the least condescending. His classes are always interesting and informative. I hope he continues to teach at the U of O for a long time to come.

Awesome professor! Extremely smart with a wide range of knowledge. Very helpful towards student that asked for face time. Interesting lectures that make you want to go home an research more... Can't say enough. Of course, he isn't full time or permanent: at Ottawa U, the really good ones never are.
AMAZING professor. Always made class interesting, very passionate, enthusiastic, makes you want to keep learning.
Great Prof, knows his stuff very well. Very insightful in the world of poetry. Was scared of the class coming in. Made it very easy to understand poetry to a person who had no passion for English!

Short stories class: he is the reason I still love English after having 3 horrible  engl. profs my first year.  He is so interesting and open minded!  I really recommend his class above anyone's at Ottawa U.  Not a hard marker and very fair on exams.  Stories he picks are so good too!
I liked this professor. His lectures were interesting and stimulating. Also, he is foxy.

Professor Howley is easily one of the best professors I've ever had. His lectures are extremely engaging and make you want to attend class.  His passion for his work is inspiring. Take any class you can with him, you will not regret it.
Very Good Prof !!!
He was very insightful, very creative and pretty insipring when it came to conjuring up essay topics. I would take a class with him again in a second.

Best prof I have ever had by far. I took this course as a Carleton-Ottawa U exchange and I am so glad I did. Fascinating course, provided very interesting insights. Very helpful and fair, good feedback on exams and papers. Very encouraging. I liked that he gave us a creative option instead of just an essay.
yes!

Awesome teacher. Take classes with him if you can, he's the best English prof you can get. Class is optional, and he seems to understand that English lectures are pointless if you don't want to be there (esp. at 5:30 on a friday).

he has a stimulating lecture style, and was very insightful. He seemed genuinely interested in the material, and the class response to it. His intelligence and humor made him very attractive. The class was actually a lot of fun!

great professor, really knows his stuff, almost too well. he is a good guy to have as a teacher but can be quite intimidating. participation not required in most classes, but it would be hard to participate anyways. his level of diction is quite high even if you read obsessively.
Great prof! Always had something really interesting to say and got the class interested. Picked a great selection of prose to look at.
hot. passionate. cute. friendly. nice jeans. nice sweaters. gorgeous eyes. class was fine.
Brilliant, very helpful and knowledgeable. Hot!
I had a crush on him :)
ok
Hurray for Ashton! Fantastic stories, contagious passion... I had a crush on him.

Awesome prof, super boring class but he made it as interesting as he could... He also realized that this was a mandatory class so he made it as easy as he could for people to get marks. Really helpful and understanding, down to earth.

Very interesting, realizes that the course is manditory and not everyone wants to take it, so trys to make it as enjoyable as possible. I've never liked english until his class. Content interesting and fairly easy marker.
O.K. class.
What a great prof.
Such a helpful prof. The readings were interesting and he always explained them in vast detail which helped alot.
A very committed teacher. Humorous and his feedback on essays is great.
worst english prof i've ever had the misfortune of taking a class with.  The class was a real let down..
This guy actually knows what he's doing. He doesn't use notes and can ENGAGE a classroom.  A very interesting prof.

easily the best english prof out there. Great at teching, open to questions and a funny charming guy. Great class, tedious stories but the novels he picked were great. watch out for the exam though. I would take his class again if it would count.
